'''伊莉莎白·安妮·「麗茲」·維拉斯奎茲'''（{{lang-en|Elizabeth Anne "Lizzie" Velásquez}}，{{IPAc-en|ˈ|l|ɪ||z|i|_|v|ə|ˈ|l|æ|s|k|ɛ|z}}；{{bd|1989年|3月13日}}） ，美國[[勵志演講人|勵志演講人]]、社會活動家、模特經紀、作家與[[YouTuber|YouTuber]]，她患有{{link-en|馬凡氏早衰脂肪營養不良症候群|Marfanoid–progeroid–lipodystrophy syndrome}}（又簡稱馬凡氏脂肪營養不良症候群，MPL），一種令其無法積存[[脂肪組織|脂肪]]與增加體重的[[罕見病|罕見病]]，除此之外還有視力受損等病徵。因著此疾病，維拉斯奎茲在童年時遭受霸凌，更被逼在青少年時期面對網路上的[[網路霸凌|暴力]]。她在成年後成為一位勵志演講人<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/education/once-bullied-now-empowered-lizzie-velasquez-lobbies-capitol-hill/2015/10/27/8f6c8ece-7ce3-11e5-afce-2afd1d3eb896_story.html?noredirect=on|title=Once bullied, now empowered, Lizzie Velasquez lobbies Capitol Hill}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://brentwoodhomepage.com/anti-bullying-activist-lizzie-velasquez-will-share-story-of-her-journey/|title=Anti-bullying activist Lizzie Velasquez will share story of her journey|date=2017-04-07|website=Brentwood Home Page|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-16}}</ref>，並以其樂觀聞名<ref name="alphonse" /><ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" />。

== 早年生活 ==
維拉斯奎茲在1989年3月13日出生於[[美國|美國]][[德克薩斯州|德克薩斯州]][[奧斯汀|奧斯汀]]<ref>{{cite web|work=Myheritage.com |url=http://www.familytreelegends.com/records/txbirths?c=search&first=elizabeth&last=velasquez+&spelling=Exact&11_year=1989&11_month=3&11_day=13&4=&14=&SubmitSearch.x=23&SubmitSearch.y=16 |title=Texas Birth Record search for Elizabeth Velasquez |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111072411/http://www.familytreelegends.com/records/txbirths?c=search&first=elizabeth&last=velasquez%2B&spelling=Exact&11_year=1989&11_month=3&11_day=13&4=&14=&SubmitSearch.x=23&SubmitSearch.y=16 |archive-date=2014-01-11 }}</ref>，是麗塔（Rita）和瓜達盧佩（Guadalupe）四個孩子中的長女<ref name = voxxi>{{Cite web |url=http://www.voxxi.com/ugliest-woman-in-the-world-true-beauty/ |title=‘Ugliest woman in the world’ teaches about true beauty |date=2012-09-19 |first=Paloma |last=Corredor |website=voxxi.com |access-date=2013-02-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130314222712/http://www.voxxi.com/ugliest-woman-in-the-world-true-beauty/ |archive-date=2013-03-14 }}</ref>。她是[[早產兒|早產兒]]，比預產期早出生四個星期，且體重不到1.219公斤<ref>{{cite web |title=Lizzie Velásquez |url=https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/4216406.Lizzie_Vel_squez |website=www.goodreads.com |access-date=2020-09-08 |ref=birth_weight}}</ref><ref name = 'abc'/>。

維拉斯奎茲從中學畢業後前往[[德克薩斯州立大學|德克薩斯州立大學]]就讀<ref name="abc">[https://abcnews.go.com/Health/Wellness/texas-woman-gain-weight-bullied/story?id=17228529 Texas Woman Can't Gain Weight, Bullied Over Looks] ''ABC News''. 2012-09-14.</ref>，主修[[傳播學|傳播學]]，並在2012年學成<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archive.star.txstate.edu/websites/star.txstate.edu/content/lizzies-story/|title=Lizzie's Story|author=Allen Reed|date=2009-12-03|publisher=University Star|access-date=2016-12-17}}</ref>。她是一位[[天主教徒|天主教徒]]，當談到自己的信仰時，其表示：「它（天主教）一直是助我渡過所有難關的支柱，當有時間獨自一人，向上帝祈禱和交談時，便知道祂就在我身邊<ref name="Walker2013">{{cite web|url=http://www.charismanews.com/us/42243-world-s-ugliest-woman-proves-that-jesus-makes-all-things-beautiful|title='World's Ugliest Woman' Proves That Jesus Makes All Things Beautiful|last=Walker|first=Ken|date=2013-12-31|publisher=Charisma|language=en|access-date=2016-06-28|quote=Raised in the Catholic parish where both her parents work, Velasquez's decision to follow Christ came near the end of high school. She credits her faith with enabling her to endure everything from scorn to physical infirmities. "It's been my rock through everything, just having the time to be alone and pray and talk to God and know that He's there for me," she says.}}</ref><ref name="Collier2014">{{cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/lizzie-velasquez-once-labeled-worlds-ugliest-woman-using-faith-in-jesus-to-spread-message-of-love-and-tolerance-video-112153/|title=Lizzie Velasquez, Once Labeled World's Ugliest Woman, Using Faith in Jesus to Spread Message of Love and Tolerance (VIDEO)|last=Collier|first=Myles|date=2014-01-07|publisher=The Christian Post|language=en|access-date=2016-06-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierchristianity.com/Past-Issues/2014/November-2014/Lizzie-Velasquez|title=Lizzie Velasquez|last=Hart|first=Lucinda van der|date=2014|publisher=Premier Christianity|language=en|access-date=2016-06-28|quote=I was born and raised in the Catholic faith and my parents have  always been very involved in church and volunteering. It was always my dad's way of wanting to say to God, 'We will be as close as we can with you, volunteer and do what we can, as long as you help keep Lizzie healthy.' And so we did that our whole lives.}}</ref>」。

== 病症 ==
維拉斯奎茲患有的[[遺傳病|遺傳病]]雖然不會致命但極其罕見，且此前從未被發現<ref name=NyDaily>{{cite news|last=Hartenstein|first=Meena|title=Lizzie Velasquez, 30-year-old with undiagnosed genetic disorder, must eat 60 times a day to survive|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/lizzie-velasquez-21-year-old-undiagnosed-genetic-disorder-eat-60-times-day-survive-article-1.184956|publisher=New York Daily|access-date=2013-06-23|location=New York}}</ref>。她的病症與許多其他病相似，尤其是[[早衰症|早衰症]]。{{link-en|德克薩斯大學達拉斯西南醫學中心|University of Texas Southwestern Medical Center}}的醫學研究人員此前曾推測該病是一種新發現的[[新生兒|新生兒]]{{link-en|早老性症候群|progeroid syndrome}}（{{link-en|魏德曼-勞滕斯特勞赫症候群|Wiedemann-Rautenstrauch syndrome}}，WR），而這種病不會影響骨骼、器官和牙齒的健康，恰與維拉斯奎茲的病徵相似<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/girl-must-eat-every-15-minutes-lizzie-velasquez-stays-skeletal-despite-nonstop-eating-pictures/ | title=Girl Must Eat Every 15 Minutes: Lizzie Velasquez Stays Skeletal Despite Nonstop Eating | work=CBS News | date=2010-06-29 | access-date=2015-03-14 | author=Freeman, David}}</ref>。

維拉斯奎茲無法增重，這是其患有的罕見病的主要特徵之一<ref name ='today'>[http://www.today.com/id/38105383/site/todayshow/ns/today-today_health/t/meet-woman-who-cant-gain-weight-shes-pounds/#.URjO3fK7ouN Meet woman who can’t gain weight: At 21, she’s 60 pounds] ''Today Health'' at today.com. 2010-07-06</ref>。她的體重從未超過29公斤（64磅），且[[體脂肪率|體脂肪率]]近乎為零<ref name="TEDxAustinWomen">{{citation|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c62Aqdlzvqk |title=How Do YOU Define Yourself Lizzie Velasquez at TEDxAustinWomen}}</ref><ref name="Telegraph2010">{{cite web | title = The girl who must eat every 15 minutes to stay alive | website = The Telegraph | date = 2010-06-28 | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/health/news/7858664/The-girl-who-must-eat-every-15-minutes-to-stay-alive.html|quote=Lizzie Velasquez weighs just four stone and has almost zero per cent body fat but she is not anorexic. [...] Despite consuming between 5,000 and 8,000 calories daily, the communications student, has never tipped over 4st 3lbs.}}</ref>。此外，維拉斯奎茲平均每天需要消耗5,000至8,000卡路里，必須一整天吃許多小餐和零食<ref name="TEDxAustinWomen" /><ref name="Telegraph2010" />。不僅如此，她的右眼[[失明|失明]]，四歲時就開始看不見事物<ref name="alphonse">[http://shine.yahoo.com/beauty/lessons-worlds-ugliest-woman-stop-staring-start-learning-184400606.html Lessons from the 'World's Ugliest Woman': 'Stop Staring and Start Learning'] by Lylah M. Alphonse of Yahoo! Shine. 2012-09-13</ref>，而左眼亦存在[[視力受損|視力受損]]的情況<ref name=About>{{cite web|last=Velasquez|first=Lizzie|title=About Lizzie|url=http://www.aboutlizzie.com/#!news/cf4g}}</ref>。

據透露在2015年左右，一位名叫艾比·所羅門（Abby Solomon）的女子與維拉斯奎茲的病情相似但不那麼嚴重，醫師在所羅門的{{link-en|蛋白質前體|proprotein}}身上發現由{{link-en|FBN1|Fibrillin 1}}[[基因|基因]][[編碼區|編碼]]的新[[激素|激素]]{{link-en|白脂素|asprosin}}存在[[突變|突變]]，最終導致她們出現無法增重等症狀<ref name="Bordo2015">{{cite AV media | people = Bordo, Sara (Director); Campo, Michael (Writer); Velasquez, Lizzie (Star) | year = 2015 | title = A Brave Heart: The Lizzie Velasquez Story | time = 45:50 to 50:36 | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bm81NWZNdpw&t=45m50s}}</ref><ref name="Kennedy2016">{{cite web | last=Kennedy | first=Pagan | title=The Thin Gene | website=The New York Times | date=2016-11-25 | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/25/opinion/sunday/the-thin-gene.html | access-date=2017-05-22}}</ref>。該病症隨後按其特性命名為{{link-en|馬凡氏早衰脂肪營養不良症候群|Marfanoid–progeroid–lipodystrophy syndrome}}（MPL），或簡稱作馬凡氏脂肪營養不良症候群（MFLS）<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Graul-Neumann LM, Kienitz T, Robinson PN, Baasanjav S, Karow B, Gillesen-Kaesbach G, Fahsold R, Schmidt H, Hoffmann K, Passarge E | title = Marfan syndrome with neonatal progeroid syndrome-like lipodystrophy associated with a novel frameshift mutation at the 3-prime terminus of the FBN1-gene | journal = Am. J. Med. Genet. | volume = 152A | pages = 2749–2755 | date = 2010 | doi = 10.1002/ajmg.a.33690 | pmid = 20979188}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors =Jacquinet A, Verloes A, Callewaert B, Coremans C, Coucke P, De Paepe A, Kornak U, Lebrun F, Lombret J, Pierard GE, Robinson PN, Symoens S, Van Maldergem L, Debray FG | title = Neonatal progeroid variant of Marfan syndrome with congenital lipodystrophy results from mutations at the 3' end of FBN1 gene | journal = Eur. J. Med. Genet. | volume = 57 | issue = 5 | pages = 230–234 | date = 2014 | pmid = 24613577| doi = 10.1016/j.ejmg.2014.02.012 }}</ref>。

== 演講家生涯 ==
自從在2006年（時年17歲）被一條發佈在YouTube的影片譏諷為「世界上最醜的女人」（World's Ugliest Woman）之後，維拉斯奎茲便公開表示自己反欺凌。她在2010年與其母親麗塔（Rita）合著，自行出版其自傳《美麗的麗茲：麗茲·維拉斯奎茲的故事》（''Lizzie Beautiful: The Lizzie Velásquez Story''），並以英文和西班牙文兩個版本發行<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/work/best_book/13805878-lizzie-beautiful-the-lizzie-velasquez-story|title=Lizzie Beautiful|website=www.goodreads.com|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref>。2014年1月，維拉斯奎茲在[[TED大會|TED]]x[[奧斯汀|Austin]]Women Talk上發表題為《如何界定你自己？》（How do you define yourself?）的演講<ref name=TED20140121>{{cite web |title=How do you define yourself? - Lizzie Velasquez at TEDxAustinWomen |url=http://tedxtalks.ted.com/video/How-do-you-define-yourself-Lizz |publisher=TED |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160809045221/http://tedxtalks.ted.com/video/How-do-you-define-yourself-Lizz |archive-date=2016-08-09 }}</ref>，並截至2021年3月20日在YouTube上已有超過1100萬次觀看<ref name=YTviews20161025>{{cite web |title=Lizzie Velasquez |url=https://www.youtube.com/user/lizzitachickita/about |publisher=YouTube (website report of video views) |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025221407/https://www.youtube.com/user/lizzitachickita/about |archive-date=2016-10-25 }}</ref>。在2015年的{{link-en|全國防止欺凌月|National Bullying Prevention Month}}，她擔任「{{link-en|旁觀者革命|Bystander Revolution}}」行動月社交媒體挑戰的主持人<ref>{{cite web|title=Lizzie Velasquez's Challenge: Born Beautiful|url=http://www.bystanderrevolution.org/monthofaction/22|website=Bystander Revolution|access-date=2016-04-20|date=2015-10-22}}</ref>

維拉斯奎茲特別針對兒童寫了兩本書，除了分享自己的故事外還為他們提供建議。2012年的《變美，做自己》（''Be Beautiful, Be You''）分享了她發現「真正使我們變得美麗的事物」的旅程，並希望讀者認識自己獨特的天賦和幸事<ref name=":0">{{cite web|last1=Velasquez|first1=Lizzie|title=Be Beautiful, Be You|url=http://www.liguori.org/be-beautiful-be-you.html|website=Liguori.org|publisher=Liguori Publications|access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref>。該書的西班牙文版本則在隔年發行<ref name=":1">{{cite web|last1=Velasquez|first1=Lizzie|title=Sé bella, sé tú misma|url=http://www.liguori.org/se-bella-se-tu-misma.html|website=Liguori.org|publisher=Liguori Publications|access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref>。另一本書是在2014年出版的《快樂是最強大的選擇》（''Choosing Happiness''） ，講述維拉斯奎茲遇到的一些阻礙，以及她如何學會在易於放棄的情況下選擇幸福的重要性<ref name=":2">{{cite web|last1=Velasquez|first1=Lizzie|title=Choosing Happiness|url=http://www.liguori.org/choosing-happiness.html|website=Liguori.org|publisher=Liguori Publications|access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref>。

維拉斯奎茲的第三本書《勇於雍容》（''Dare to be Kind''）在2017年發行，內容有關其在現實和網上受到欺凌的親身經歷，並從而闡述厚道的重要性<ref>{{cite web|title=Dare to Be Kind: How Extraordinary Compassion Can Transform Our World|url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-316-27243-8|website=publishersweekly.com|publisher=PWxyz, LLC|access-date=2017-11-06}}</ref>。她的紀錄片《勇敢的心：維拉斯奎茲的故事》（''A Brave Heart: The Lizzie Velásquez Story''） 則在2015年3月14日於[[西南偏南|西南偏南]]上首映<ref name="hawkins">{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-ouch-30948179 | title='Bullies called me the world's ugliest woman online' | work=BBC News | date=2015-03-14 | access-date=2015-03-14 | author=Hawkins, Kathleen}}</ref>。維拉斯奎茲隨後在2017年4月開始主演其原創的{{link-en|Fullscreen|Fullscreen (company)}}節目《解壓縮》（''Unzipped''）<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.raredr.com/news/lizzie-velasquez-show-body-positivity|title=No More Bullying: Lizzie Velasquez Has New Show About Body Positivity|website=Rare Disease Report|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Unzipped with Lizzie Velasquez|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt6614948/|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref>。

